            <title>[HBASE-14170] [HBase Rest] RESTServer is not shutting down if &quot;hbase.rest.port&quot; Address already in use.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14170</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;HBase Rest&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; RESTServer is not shutting down if &quot;hbase.rest.port&quot; Address already in use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; If &quot;hbase.rest.port&quot; Address already in use, RESTServer should shutdown,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;with out this &quot;hbase.rest.port&quot;  we cant perform any operations on RESTServer. Then there is no use of running RESTServer process.&lt;/p&gt;

